        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): honor outbound reaction directives",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Parse Telegram reaction directives without leaking them into visible chat text.\r\n- Preserve reaction intent in structured `channelData.telegram.reaction`.\r\n- Support reaction-only replies when a valid target exists.\r\n- Use Telegram's native reaction API instead of simulating the behavior in text.\r\n- Reject missing targets and unsuccessful reaction delivery.\r\n\r\n## Linked context\r\n\r\nCloses #71140\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\n- Behavior addressed: Telegram reaction directives now normalize into native reaction payloads instead of leaking as visible text or being dropped.\r\n- Real environment tested: OpenClaw Telegram SUT on macOS source checkout, with focused Vitest coverage for the production reply normalization and Telegram delivery paths.\r\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\r\n\r\n```text\r\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/reply-delivery.test.ts src/infra/outbound/payloads.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/outbound-adapter.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot/delivery.test.ts\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Evidence after fix:\r\n\r\n```text\r\nTest Files  4 passed (4)\r\nTests       134 passed (134)\r\n[test] passed 3 Vitest shards\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Observed result after fix: Reaction directives are stripped from visible text, reaction-only payloads reach the Telegram reaction API, and rejected or targetless reactions are not reported as successful delivery.\r\n- What was not tested: A live Telegram account was not exercised from this source checkout. The linked issue contains live Telegram reproduction and prior installed-build validation.\r\n- Negative control / before evidence: Current `main` does not parse reaction directives into structured channel data and rejects reaction-only replies as missing text/media.\r\n\r\n## Tests and validation\r\n\r\n- Targeted Vitest: 134 tests passed\r\n- Focused core and Telegram lint passed\r\n- Formatting check passed\r\n- `git diff --check` passed\r\n- Core-to-plugin boundary check passed\r\n\r\n## Risk checklist\r\n\r\n- Did user-visible behavior change? Yes\r\n- Did config, environment, or migration behavior change? No\r\n- Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? No\r\n- Highest-risk area: Telegram reaction-only delivery\r\n- Mitigation: Focused parser, normalization, adapter, invalid-reaction, and delivery regression tests\r\n\r\n## Current review state\r\n\r\n- AI-assisted: Yes, Codex\r\n- Next action: Awaiting maintainer review\r\n- Bot comments addressed: None yet\r\n",
